ng von Sozialarbeiter*innen in Österreich. Sie zeigt, wie dringend notwendige Kompetenzen zur Bewältigung der zunehmend komplexen Berufspraxis entwickelt werden.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aBildung. 4aBildungsforschung. 4aBildungspolitik. 4aGlobal Citizenship Education. 4aMenschenrechte. 4aProfessionsethik. 4aPädagogik. 4aSozialarbeit. 4aSoziale Arbeit. 4aTransformation. 7aEDUCATION / Organizations & Institutions.2bisacsh  aEducation.  aEducational Policy.  aEducational Research.  aGlobal Citizenship Education.  aHuman Rights.  aPedagogy.  aProfessional Ethic.  aSocial Work.  aTransformation.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2024z9783111332376oZDB-23-TGP40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839470206?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839470206zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839470206/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA  aZDB-23-TGPb2024